# SumelaOS — EXTRA documentation ingest dirs (PROJECT-OWNED, optional).
#
# Copy this file to `.sumela/ingest.conf` (same dir, drop the `.example`) and list
# directories whose Markdown docs you want included in the Qdrant `wiki_pages`
# Tier-1 semantic index — IN ADDITION to docs/second-brain/wiki/. Useful for
# authoritative reference docs that live elsewhere in the repo (architecture docs,
# ADRs, API references) without copying them into the wiki (which would drift).
#
# Rules:
#   * One repo-relative directory per line. `#` comments and blank lines are ignored.
#   * Repo-relative ONLY — no absolute paths, `~`, `..`, globs, or drive letters.
#     Anything that escapes the repo root is rejected (symlink targets included).
#   * Docs only: only `.md` files are ingested. The code corpus is NOT affected.
#   * Default is EMPTY — with no `.sumela/ingest.conf` (and no EXTRA_INGEST_DIRS
#     env var), only the wiki is ingested.
#   * `.sumela/ingest.conf` is TRACKED and shared with your team. Adding a path is a
#     trust decision (a teammate's pull will background-ingest it) — in team mode,
#     protect this file via CODEOWNERS, the same as a git hook.
#   * Override per-shell/CI with the env var EXTRA_INGEST_DIRS (comma- or
#     colon-separated); when set non-empty it takes precedence over this file.
#
# Examples (uncomment / edit):
# docs/architecture
# docs/adr
# api/reference
